description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic, motivated individual to join our experienced team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We actively encourage applications from people with experience of working within a community mental health care setting. We are looking for individuals who have experience of working within mental health and are able to engage and work with people in a practical way that enables recovery in both people with dementia and functional mental health difficulties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will receive supervision from within the team monthly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally we would like applicants to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* NVQ at Level 2 in health and social care or equivalent relevant training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Good written and verbal communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Good IT skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Willing to complete training on the Trust&#96;s electronic clinical records system (RIO)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Ability to work on your own and willing to develop skills and abilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Be outgoing and enthusiastic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Work well as part of a team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Their own lived experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work with clients, in their own homes, and will be expected to co-facilitate some practical groups and activities if required, both within the service and in the local community. The post holder will be expected to work 9-5 Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your commitment, we offer excellent opportunities for personal development through supervision and appraisal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
